Ending - Collecting all 5 question marks puts the game into Turbo Mode.


Super Sound Test - First go the the player/skill select screen and then
press the two top buttons on the controller in this order: L, R, L, L, R.
You will hear the voice say, "BINGO" and then you will be brought to the
theme music section and sound select screen!


SUPER SOCCER
============ 
Passcodes - These passcodes allow you to access special features: by keying
in up/right, up/left, right, down/left, right, right, up, right, you can
set up a match between two computer controlled teams and watch the game.

If you're looking for a challenge, you can access the Expert mode by entering
up/right, down/left, right, down, down/right, left, down/left, up/left.

NOTE: diagonal key presses are indicated by pairs like up/right. 


SUPER SOCCER CHAMP
=================
Recruit a talented team full of Ace Strikers onto your side by doing the
following. When the title screen appears, press the directions on the Control
Pad and the controller buttons in the following order: Up, X, Left, Y,
Right, A, Down, B, Left, Up, Right, Down, Select, Start. Then choose your
team and your selected Ace Striker. When you start the game, all the members
of your team will play with the speed and finesse of Ace Strikers.


SUPER STAR WARS                                                  
===============
99 Extra Lives - In the Land of the Sand People, there are 2 sets of floating
rocks, in  which you have to jump from rock to rock to get to the other cliff.
At the very beginning of the second set you come too, jump off the cliff edge,
and aim Luke to the left. You will land on a ledge, and you will be in a small
cave area. Falling rocks will keep falling on you, but don't worry about that.
Now shot up in the air all over the place to reveal 1-UPs. There are 7 or 9 of
them. Get them all and then commit suicide. When the game starts up again, you
start at the cliff top again. Jump down and repeat until you have 99 lives.

Sound Test & Special Code Screen - The sound test screen is also a way to
find different codes for the game. After choosing the Start Game option from
the title screen, go to the first level. Hold down all Y, B, X, and A 
buttons simultanously and while holding these, hit the START button. It 
should bring up the Sound Test screen. Change the music to what you like.
Go back into the sound test again by doing the same trick, and you will see
that the words under SOUND TEST have changed. Repeat this trick for different
messages. The first one will tell you to press X, B, B, A, Y for 5 continues.
The second will tell you to press Y, Y, X, X, A, B, X, A for the light saber.
To work these codes, turn your Super NES off and then on again. Do the code
of your choice at the title screen when the "Start Game" and "Options" choice
comes up. You will hear the Jawa yell if the trick has worked. If you reset
the game and try these tricks, they will not work. You must turn the power
off and on again for the tricks to work properly.


SUPER TENNIS
============
Start in Final Game - To see the ending screen and be a winner in every
tournament as 'AMY', enter the first code below.  You will have to win
the New York Open, which is the final game.  The second set of codes
will get you to the championship with the maximum number of points.

08QCMVF RHRMSYY         K8Xd3Hr Ftlwjpc
RHYH9QX J0VYQYH         Zgnybq1 4065C6P
4HR0CQ1 4065C6P         Djstk8X D3Hrftl
DJSSSRL MM8             Wjpukmw Igg

Advanced Player - Start the game like normal, but when you begin, press
SELECT on controller 1 before you serve.  Now on controller 2, press these
buttons in this order:  R, R, LEFT, DOWN, B, A, L and L.  You should then
hear the crowd cheer.  Back on controller 1, press A or B and you should
see some numbers and letters on the screen.  Change all of these numbers
and letters to the letter F using the X and B buttons on controller 1, and
you will have a pro who is fast and very accurate.

The numbers actually mean something. If the number at the top of the screen
is a 0, the digits relate to the abilities of Player One. If it is a 1, you
are looking at the abilities of the player on the other side of the net.
(Player Two in a competitive match). If the number is a 2, these are the
abilities of Player One's partner. A number 3 is for the partner of the
player on the other side of the net. You can change the number at the top of
the screen with the A Button.
The letters and numbers which signify the abilities of a player are arranged
in four rows of eight digits which range from 0 to 9, then A to F, 0 being
the lowest and F the highest (Hexidecimal numbers). The numbers and letters
on the top row relate to the player's strength and speed. Digits on the 
second and third rows relate to the player's intelligence (only if the player
is computer controlled). You can change any of the digits. First single them
out with the Control Pad and tap the X button. Then press the Select Button
to return to the game. 

Power Player - On the Player Select screen, highlight the name of the player
that you intend to choose. Then on Controller II, press the L button five
times, the X button once, the R button seven times, and the X button once
again. When you begin playing with the highlighted pro, you'll have
incredible speed and power and you'll easily march through the rounds of the
tournament.


TEENAGE MUTANT NINJA TURTLES IV
===============================
Increase to 10 lives - On title screen, using controller 2, enter the follow-
ing code:  UP, UP, DOWN, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT, B, A.  Next, go to the options
screen with controller 1 and you should be able to increase your number of
lives even further to 10 lives.


THUNDER SPIRITS
===============
Option Screen - This is an option mode trick.  Hold the L button on the top
of the controller and the SELECT button at the same time.  While holding
these, press START and you will be brought to an option screen which will
give you many features to improve your game.

NOTE: Nintendo Power says you can access the special Configuration Screen 
from the title screen by pressing and holding the Select button and pressing
the Start button. You can change the number of points needed for a bonus ship
and add to your starting number of ships. Since the configuration mode 
changes after you have completed a game, wait for the title screen to 
reappear and reset your options.

Extra Credits - Whille the tittle screen is showing, tab the B button
quickly and repeatedly. If you are very fast, you'll trigger an occasional
tone. For every tone that you hear, you'll earn an extra game credit. Now
press Start to play.


